From 3319894844c554856461dfc32aea4f32cd0eb608 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew George <matt.george.receipts@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:41:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Section 17 / Figure 15: donor structure under
 Copalis-Mocrocks co-management

New RMD section quantifies the Section 11.6 caveat: Copalis and Mocrocks are the
donor for ~63% of Long Beach / Twin Harbors imputed days and interleave under the
state-Quinault 2-on/2-off day trade. Pulling state sampling to 45% raises single-day
imputation error 0.45 -> 0.50 (same-day donor coverage 99% -> 45%); sharing the tribe's
alternate-day counts holds it at 0.40. Fig 15 added to sampling_design.
---
